.SH NAME
RTCSctpTransport.maxMessageSize \- RTCSctpTransport: maxMessageSize
property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]maxMessageSize\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]RTCSctpTransport\f[R] interface indicates the maximum size of a
message that can be sent using the \f[CR]RTCDataChannel.send()\f[R]
method.
.SH VALUE
An integer value giving the maximum size, in bytes, of a message which
can be sent using the \f[CR]RTCDataChannel.send()\f[R] method.
.SH EXAMPLES
This example shows how you might split up a string into small enough
parts to send based on maximum message size.
.IP
.EX
// Function splits strings to a specified size and returns array.
function splitStringToMax(str, maxLength) {
  const result = [];
  let i = 0;
  while (i < str.length) {
    result.push(str.substring(i, i + maxLength));
    i += maxLength;
  }
  return result;
}

const peerConnection = new RTCPeerConnection(options);
const channel = peerConnection.createDataChannel(\[dq]chat\[dq]);
channel.onopen = (event) => {
  const maximumMessageSize = peerConnection.sctp.maxMessageSize;
  const textToSend = \[dq]This is my possibly overly long string!\[dq];
  splitStringToMax(textToSend, maximumMessageSize).forEach((elem) => {
    channel.send(elem);
  });
};
